    "body": "This is a BIP draft for full-aggregation of BIP340 Schnorr signatures, a standard for the [DahLIAS scheme](https://eprint.iacr.org/2025/692) by Jonas Nick, Tim Ruffing, and Yannick Seurin. It complements [BIP458 half-aggregation](https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/pull/2205). Full-aggregation results in a constant 64-byte signature but requires an interactive signing protocol.\r\n\r\nCompared to the version [shared on the mailing list](https://groups.google.com/g/bitcoindev/c/TF5mPfy58RQ) recently, this version incorporates waxwing's feedback from the thread, most notably:\r\n\r\n1. More info on the uniqueness check in `Sign` and new test vectors covering this and other checks\r\n2. A description of the deterministic nonce attack\r\n3. Clarifications on the security model and other language improvements for clarity\r\n\r\nThe reference implementation is written in Python based on secp256k1lab, and the latest master of secp256k1lab is vendored with the BIP, same as it was done for BIP458.",
